---
description: How Cursor should work on Godot port tasks in this project.
alwaysApply: true
---

Before coding:

- Start from [docs/DOC_INDEX.md](docs/DOC_INDEX.md); use README_00–05 for design intent.
- Check [docs/GODOT_PORT_STATUS.md](docs/GODOT_PORT_STATUS.md) and [docs/IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md](docs/IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md) — do not assume PDF features are built.
- Respect **Khan 1 gate** ([README_00](docs/README_00_MASTER_PROJECT_INDEX.md)): no full campaign art, maps 2–8 polish, or launch monetization unless the task explicitly scopes it.
- Identify the smallest useful change; ask only if a decision blocks implementation.
- Unity parity: compare `_archive/unity/Assets/_Project/` when requested — paths and APIs differ.

When coding:

- Work in `shahname-td-godot/shahname-td/` unless the task is shared `/docs` or cross-cutting design.
- Keep changes focused; prefer new files over large rewrites when safe.
- Preserve public APIs unless the task requires changing them.
- Reference content by **stable resource IDs**, not display names or filename guessing ([README_04](docs/README_04_DEVELOPMENT_PRODUCTION_ROADMAP.md)).
- Update docs when architecture or data contracts change; update `GODOT_PORT_STATUS.md` for port milestones.
- Do not wire new **paid power**, battle pass, or forced ads — align with [README_03](docs/README_03_ETHICAL_MONETIZATION_BUSINESS.md).
- TODO comments only for real follow-up work.

After coding:

- Summarize changed files.
- Test steps: Godot 4.6 → open project → F5/F6 → expected behavior + edge cases.
- Mention known limitations vs design canon.
- Suggest next step aligned to milestones M0–M8 (usually M1–M4 until Khan 1 replay is proven).

Do not invent final art. Use `art/_placeholders/` and mark placeholders clearly.
